 donor\nradius is most consistent with He-star progenitors, although the observed\nspectral features seem to contradict this. The discovery of 5 new eclipsing\nAM~CVn systems is consistent with the known observed AM CVn space density and\nestimated ZTF recovery efficiency. Based on this estimate, we expect to find\nanother 1--4 eclipsing AM CVn systems as ZTF continues to obtain data. This\nwill further increase our understanding of the population, but will require\nhigh precision data to better characterize these 5 systems and any new\ndiscoveries.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Jul 2021 19:10:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 30 Aug 2021 19:37:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-01"}
