pressure fluctuation scaling with Mach number\n$\\sigma_{\\ln{\\bar{P}}}^2\\approx\\ln(1+b^2\\gamma^2\\mathcal{M}^4)$ is unaffected\nby thermal instability and is the same as in hydro turbulence. In contrast, the\ndensity fluctuations characterised by $\\sigma_s^2$ are much larger, especially\nfor $\\mathcal{M}\\lesssim0.5$. In magnetohydrodynamic runs, magnetic fields\nprovide significant pressure support in the cold phase but do not have any\nstrong effects on the diffuse gas distribution, and nature and amplitude of\nfluctuations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 Jul 2021 06:31:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 9 Dec 2021 04:05:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-10"}
